cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the performance of cellular networks, which is a subfield of networking. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives the spectral efficiency and outage probability of downlink transmission, which are concepts related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper develops a systematic framework to analyze the performance of cellular systems with BS sleeping, which can be considered as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers the impact of user association and scheduling on the downlink performance, which is related to multimedia traffic. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper considers two user association schemes and compares their performance, which can be considered as a game-theoretic problem.
